      "id": 5247,
      "name": "Mr Daniel David Emery",
      "username": "Emmodd",
      "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/e/34f0e0/{size}.png",
      "created_at": "2022-01-24T11:04:16.879Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Hi all.</p>\n<p>Is there a way to use the above and limit the training time per week (so that the functional overload is caused by increasing intensity rather than time)? It seems that the increased training stress is implemented by a combo of both more intensity and time as things stand.</p>\n<p>If a person has only so much time to train a week then then how can I continue to improve without the training time going up and up - or can\u2019t I? Do I need to adjust ramp rate/intensity upward whilst keeping the hrs at the start of a block the same?</p>\n<p>Many thanks.</p>",
