      "username": "Emmodd",
      "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/e/34f0e0/{size}.png",
      "created_at": "2022-01-24T15:28:13.500Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Thanks guys.</p>\n<p>To expand, if I\u2019m never going to be able to train more than say 8 hrs a week then either I get the stimulus to keep improving by adding more intensity or else I reach a ceiling and am just maintaining.</p>\n<p>There shouldn\u2019t be a risk of overtraining given the fact that it\u2019s only 8hrs of training and so with gradual increases intensity and plenty of rest (which an 8 hr week should allow) I should in theory be able to continue to get stronger (obviously up to a point).</p>\n<p>I wonder if the adaptive training will ultimately help pay into this?</p>",
