      "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forums.trainerday.com/aguti00/{size}/675_2.png",
      "created_at": "2022-01-24T15:51:09.721Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Of course it is possible to continue improving with 8 hours a week. I train 8 hours a week and I\u2019m a decent cyclist (4.1 FTP) in the base phase, obviously it\u2019s not just training, it\u2019s rest, good nutrition, consistency, fun, etc.</p>\n<p>This is a typical week of mine, (last week)</p>\n<p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/original/1X/dce097a6e4155361baf26915c2c2285a4b2c7c35.png\" data-download-href=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/dce097a6e4155361baf26915c2c2285a4b2c7c35\" title=\"image\"><img src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/1X/dce097a6e4155361baf26915c2c2285a4b2c7c35_2_690x178.png\" alt=\"image\" data-base62-sha1=\"vvYehWPXMZRPwiqs26pLAs03i8l\" width=\"690\" height=\"178\" srcset=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/1X/dce097a6e4155361baf26915c2c2285a4b2c7c35_2_690x178.png, https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/1X/dce097a6e4155361baf26915c2c2285a4b2c7c35_2_1035x267.png 1.5x, https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/original/1X/dce097a6e4155361baf26915c2c2285a4b2c7c35.png 2x\" data-small-upload=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/1X/dce097a6e4155361baf26915c2c2285a4b2c7c35_2_10x10.png\"><div class=\"meta\"><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use xlink:href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">image</span><span class=\"informations\">1220\u00d7315 30.5 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use xlink:href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>\n<p>and this is the PCM, where you can see the constant progression with coach jack.</p>\n<p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/original/1X/b504cf1915ccf01231e4a66d05db8fdfea8339f7.png\" data-download-href=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/b504cf1915ccf01231e4a66d05db8fdfea8339f7\" title=\"image\"><img src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/1X/b504cf1915ccf01231e4a66d05db8fdfea8339f7_2_690x463.png\" alt=\"image\" data-base62-sha1=\"pPmIYbRKOCAwOeMcXYwSaLTzffx\" width=\"690\" height=\"463\" srcset=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/1X/b504cf1915ccf01231e4a66d05db8fdfea8339f7_2_690x463.png, https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/1X/b504cf1915ccf01231e4a66d05db8fdfea8339f7_2_1035x694.png 1.5x, https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/original/1X/b504cf1915ccf01231e4a66d05db8fdfea8339f7.png 2x\" data-small-upload=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/1X/b504cf1915ccf01231e4a66d05db8fdfea8339f7_2_10x10.png\"><div class=\"meta\"><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use xlink:href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">image</span><span class=\"informations\">1164\u00d7782 164 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use xlink:href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>\n<p>So yes, it is possible to improve with adaptive training.</p>",
