    {
      "id": 5268,
      "name": "",
      "username": "Alex",
      "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forums.trainerday.com/alex/{size}/1331_2.png",
      "created_at": "2022-01-24T19:45:59.013Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Andres, there is no way I could have answered this as well as you have.  <img src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/images/emoji/twitter/slight_smile.png?v=9\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\"></p>\n<p>I think we all have been trained we need to do the maximum amount of time and effort possible.  I have 8-hours so I should always train 8-hours for example.  Unlearning that is not easy.  Just like saying I should always do as much TSS as possible.  The right variation causes gains/adaption even when you are doing less some of the time.</p>\n<p>I really like when you said this\u2026</p>\n<p>\u201cobviously it\u2019s not just training, it\u2019s rest, good nutrition, consistency, fun, etc.\u201d</p>",
      "post_number": 8,
      "post_type": 1,
      "updated_at": "2022-01-24T19:46:51.022Z",
