    {
      "id": 5290,
      "name": "",
      "username": "Alex",
      "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forums.trainerday.com/alex/{size}/1331_2.png",
      "created_at": "2022-01-25T07:57:03.628Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Oh yes, this now makes more sense and as usual I mostly agree, but something my pro coach friend clarified a while back is that he has proven with his athletes that quality volume variability by itself creates adaption.  So small weekly/monthly variations cause mini-build cycles.  So don\u2019t build to 8-hours and stick there for long periods.</p>\n<p>Secondly regarding a clarification on increasing intensity is you can build intensity but still keep most of your training at a less than ~80% level. CJ takes this approach.</p>\n<p>Since this cycle is usually about 20-30 weeks you realistically only get about 2 of these periods a year and this may not work well for many outdoor cyclists that just want to enjoy their performance level from spring to fall.</p>\n<p>So below is visually this is what I am suggesting above. The red line represents CTL</p>\n<p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/original/1X/11106af98e1192d6a8ed15925e5461bdc62a8f9a.png\" data-download-href=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/11106af98e1192d6a8ed15925e5461bdc62a8f9a\" title=\"image\"><img src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/1X/11106af98e1192d6a8ed15925e5461bdc62a8f9a_2_690x267.png\" alt=\"image\" data-base62-sha1=\"2qXi6V1XFxDXM9Q6bVooIP9Gfai\" width=\"690\" height=\"267\" srcset=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/1X/11106af98e1192d6a8ed15925e5461bdc62a8f9a_2_690x267.png, https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/original/1X/11106af98e1192d6a8ed15925e5461bdc62a8f9a.png 1.5x, https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/original/1X/11106af98e1192d6a8ed15925e5461bdc62a8f9a.png 2x\" data-small-upload=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/1X/11106af98e1192d6a8ed15925e5461bdc62a8f9a_2_10x10.png\"><div class=\"meta\"><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use xlink:href=\"#far-image\"></use>